<h4>
    The Full Spectrum
</h4>

<p>
    As we learned in a <a href = '/pod/cf1f01'>previous pod</a>,
    the entire electromagnetic spectrum consists not of seven types of waves, but 12.
    There are the six invisible electromagnetic waves: radio, micro, infrared, ultraviolet, X-Ray, and gamma ray.
    In the middle of them, with wavelengths between 400 nanometers and 700 nanometers
    is visible light, which can be broken into six colors: red, orange, yellow, green, blue, and violet.
    Any photon has a wavelength that will classify it into one of these twelve waves.
</p>

